            <h2>Adverbs, Conjunctions, and Prepositions Overview</h2>
            <p><span class="initial-letter darkorange-text">W</span>hile adverbs, conjunctions, and prepositions
                are often small words, the impact they can have on how you translate a sentence can be quite
                significant.
            </p>
            <h3>Adverbs</h3>
            <p>Adverbs are words that describe verbs, adjectives, and other adverbs in more detail. Unlike nouns and
                adjectives, Old English adverbs are uninflected for case, gender, or number. Adverbs do have comparative
                and superlative forms, which are made by dropping the final vowel in the adverb and adding
                '<strong>or</strong>' or '<strong>ost</strong>'.</p>
